{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SFNPztg4qXhAcgYUzx2och","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have the complete integration test file. Let me provide a comprehensive summary of the patterns:\n\n## Integration Test Patterns — Complete Analysis\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n\n### Setup & Teardown Patterns\n\n**beforeAll (lines 301–391):**\n- Creates raw postgres connection\n- TRUNCATES all test tables (referral, reward, points, etc.)\n- Creates minimal test schema for referral tables (in case migration schema is incomplete)\n- Initializes DB wrapper via `createDb(DATABASE_URL, rawSql)`\n\n**beforeEach (lines 398–449):**\n- **TRUNCATE**: Clears all game-related tables with CASCADE:\n  ```sql\n  TRUNCATE rounds, closecall_rounds, closecall_candles, operator_events, \n           event_queue, game_entries, transactions, player_profiles, \n           referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims,\n           referral_kol_rates, reward_pool_fundings, point_grants, player_points,\n           dogpile_events, crate_drops RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE\n  ```\n- **Pool reset**: `UPDATE reward_pool SET balance_lamports = 0, lifetime_funded = 0, lifetime_paid = 0`\n- **Cache reset**: `resetPlatformConfigCache()`\n- **Fresh MockConnection** with pre-populated accounts:\n  - Entropy account (32 bytes)\n  - Coinflip config PDA\n  - PlatformConfig PDA with fee_bps=500 (5%)\n- **Hono app setup**: Routes mounted with JWT middleware\n\n**afterAll (lines 393–396):**\n- Closes DB and postgres connection\n\n---\n\n### Handler Call Patterns\n\n#### 1. **Settlement handlers** (lines 451–628)\nDirect settlement call via `settleMatch()`:\n```typescript\nawait settleMatch({\n  db,\n  connection: mockConn,\n  serverKeypair,\n  entropyAccount,\n  referralDefaultRateBps: 1000,\n}, matchPda);\n```\n\n#### 2. **Worker discovery + settlement** (lines 537–568)\nUses settlement worker with retry settler:\n```typescript\nconst retrySettler = createRetrySettler({\n  db,\n  connection: mockConn,\n  settleRound: (pda) => settleMatch(..., pda),\n});\n\nconst worker = createSettlementWorker({\n  db,\n  connection: mockConn,\n  serverKey: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  pollIntervalMs: 60_000,\n  onSettleReady: (pda) => {\n    settlePromise = retrySettler.attemptSettle(pda);\n    return settlePromise;\n  },\n});\n\nawait worker.poll(); // Single poll\nif (settlePromise) await settlePromise;\n```\n\n#### 3. **Event queue handlers** (lines 1278–1441)\nCalled directly with event payload:\n```typescript\n// REWARD_POOL_FUND\nconst handler = createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db });\nawait handler({ roundId, feeLamports });\n\n// POINTS_GRANT\nconst handler = createPointsGrantHandler({ db, getSolPrice });\nawait handler({\n  userId, wallet, sourceType, sourceId,\n  amountLamports, settledAt,\n});\n\n// CRATE_DROP\nconst handler = createCrateDropHandler({ db, rollRng });\nawait handler({ userId, wallet, triggerType, triggerId });\n```\n\n---\n\n### Event Queue Verification Patterns\n\n**Query events from event_queue:**\n```typescript\nconst events = await rawSql`\n  SELECT * FROM event_queue WHERE event_type = 'game.settled'\n`;\nexpect(events.length).toBe(1);\n\nconst evt = events[0]!;\nexpect(evt.status).toBe(\"pending\");\n\n// Extract payload (may be JSON string or object)\nconst payload = evt.payload as any;\nexpect(payload.roundId).toBe(matchId);\nexpect(payload.game).toBe(\"coinflip\");\n```\n\n**Verify payload structure (lines 1017–1062):**\n```typescript\nexpect(payload).toMatchObject({\n  roundId: string,\n  roundPda: string,\n  game: \"coinflip\" | \"closecall\",\n  feeLamports: string,\n  settledAt: string,\n  players: Array<{\n    wallet: string,\n    userId: string,\n    isCreator: boolean,\n    amountLamports: string,\n    isWinner: boolean,\n    payoutLamports: string,\n  }>\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### DB State Verification Patterns\n\n**Rounds (lines 489–498):**\n```typescript\nconst round = await db.getRoundByPda(matchPda);\nexpect(round!.phase).toBe(\"created\");\nexpect(round!.game).toBe(\"coinflip\");\nexpect(round!.creator).toBe(wallet);\nexpect(round!.commitment.toString(\"hex\")).toBe(commitmentHex);\n```\n\n**Operator events (lines 501–504):**\n```typescript\nconst events = await rawSql`\n  SELECT * FROM operator_events WHERE pda = ${matchPda} ORDER BY id\n`;\nexpect(eventTypes).toContain(\"secret_generated\");\nexpect(eventTypes).toContain(\"settle_confirmed\");\n```\n\n**Referral earnings (lines 803–829):**\n```typescript\nconst earnings = await rawSql`\n  SELECT * FROM referral_earnings WHERE referee_user_id = ${opponentUserId}\n`;\nexpect(earnings[0]).toMatchObject({\n  referrer_user_id: referrerUserId,\n  wager_lamports: AMOUNT_LAMPORTS,\n  fee_lamports: 250_000,\n  referrer_earned_lamports: 25_000,\n  referrer_rate_bps: 1000,\n  referee_rebate_lamports: 25_000,\n});\n```\n\n**Reward pool (lines 1289–1328):**\n```typescript\nconst poolBefore = await rawSql`\n  SELECT balance_lamports, lifetime_funded FROM reward_pool WHERE id = 1\n`;\nexpect(BigInt(poolBefore[0]!.balance_lamports)).toBe(0n);\n```\n\n**Point grants (lines 1387–1416):**\n```typescript\nconst grants = await rawSql`\n  SELECT user_id, wallet, source_type, source_id, amount, metadata\n  FROM point_grants WHERE user_id = ${userId}\n`;\nexpect(grants[0]).toMatchObject({\n  source_type: \"wager\",\n  amount: expectedPoints.toString(),\n});\n\nconst pp = await rawSql`\n  SELECT balance, lifetime_earned FROM player_points WHERE user_id = ${userId}\n`;\nexpect(BigInt(pp[0]!.balance)).toBe(expectedPoints);\n```\n\n---\n\n### CRATE_DROP Handler Tests (lines 1532–1754)\n\n**SOL Crate Hit (lines 1532–1592):**\n- Pool must be >= `10_000_000 / 0.10 = 100_000_000` (100M lamports)\n- Roll < 0.01 (1%) triggers SOL crate\n- Expected payout: `floor(pool_balance * 0.10)`\n- Creates crate_drops row with status=\"pending\"\n- Decrements pool & increments lifetime_paid\n- Emits `crate.sol_payout` event\n\n**Points Crate Hit (lines 1594–1641):**\n- Roll >= 0.01 but < 0.06 (5%) triggers points crate\n- Uses second RNG call: `min + floor(roll * (max - min + 1))`\n  - Range: 500–5000 points\n  - Example: 500 + floor(0.5 × 4501) = 2750\n- Creates crate_drops row with crate_type=\"points\"\n- Emits `points.grant` event with sourceType=\"crate_points\"\n\n**Miss (lines 1643–1672):**\n- Roll >= 0.06 → no crate created, no events\n\n**Suppression (lines 1674–1706):**\n- Pool can't fund minimum (payout < 10M) → crate not recorded\n\n**Idempotency (lines 1708–1753):**\n- Duplicate trigger (same triggerId) → only one crate row\n- Pool balance unchanged on retry\n- Uses (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id) as natural key\n\n---\n\n### Key Patterns Summary\n\n1. **DB isolation**: TRUNCATE all tables, reset reward_pool singleton\n2. **Mock setup**: Pre-populate accounts, set platform fees at test start\n3. **Handler invocation**: Pass dependencies (db, connection, RNG) to handlers\n4. **Event verification**: Query event_queue by event_type, verify payload JSON structure\n5. **Idempotency testing**: Call handler twice, verify no duplicates via natural keys\n6. **State assertions**: Use BigInt for lamports, check DB rows before/after operations"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0816eb3-ec81-48b4-9f7e-e95cff86009e","uuid":"4694d3d0-519e-41f4-83b3-4c3f20267be5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:12:07.231Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the integration test patterns for the challenge engine. Please show me the contents of:\n\n1. `backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` — the full test file, especially:\n   - How tests set up DB state (TRUNCATE, seeding)\n   - How tests call handlers\n   - How tests verify events in event_queue\n   - The beforeEach/afterAll patterns\n   - The most recent tests (CRATE_DROP handler tests at the bottom)\n\nSho