{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BjFVkGqa3nnge3wfvNTvkn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have the full picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary for you:\n\n## Database Schema & DB Client Reference\n\nHere's the complete information you need for implementing the GAME_SETTLED handler:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Challenge Engine Migration (011_challenge_engine.sql)**\n\n**File path:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql`\n\n#### **Key Tables:**\n\n**`challenge_assignments`** (lines 84-99)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `user_id` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `challenge_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to challenges)\n- `period_key` — TEXT NOT NULL (e.g., \"2026-04-03:daily\")\n- `status` — TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active' (CHECK: 'active', 'completed', 'expired')\n- `progress` — INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n- `target` — INT NOT NULL\n- `assigned_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n- `expires_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ\n- `completed_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ\n- **UNIQUE constraint:** `(user_id, challenge_id, period_key)`\n- **Indexes:** `idx_assignments_active` on `(user_id, status)` WHERE status='active'; `idx_assignments_period` on `(period_key, status)`\n\n**`progress_events`** (lines 102-111)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `assignment_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to challenge_assignments)\n- `round_id` — TEXT NOT NULL (from game settlement)\n- `user_id` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `progress_delta` — INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 1\n- `metadata` — JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'\n- `created_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n- **UNIQUE constraint:** `(assignment_id, round_id)` — **prevents duplicate progress from same game**\n\n**`challenges`** (lines 65-81)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `campaign_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to campaigns)\n- `title` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `description` — TEXT\n- `action` — TEXT NOT NULL (e.g., \"game_completed\", \"game_won\", \"lobby_filled\")\n- `scope` — TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'any' (CHECK: 'any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')\n- `condition` — TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'count'\n- `threshold` — INT NOT NULL\n- `reward_type` — TEXT NOT NULL (CHECK: 'points', 'crate')\n- `reward_amount` — INT\n- `prerequisite_id` — BIGINT (self-referential FK, nullable)\n- `eligible_if` — JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'\n- `sort_order` — INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n- `is_active` — BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true\n- `created_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n\n**`campaigns`** (lines 53-62)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `name` — TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE\n- `campaign_type` — TEXT NOT NULL (CHECK: 'daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding', 'dogpile')\n- `starts_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ\n- `ends_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ\n- `is_active` — BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true\n- `config` — JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'\n- `created_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n\n**`completion_bonuses`** (lines 114-124)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `campaign_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to campaigns)\n- `title` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `description` — TEXT\n- `required_count` — INT NOT NULL\n- `reward_type` — TEXT NOT NULL (CHECK: 'points', 'crate')\n- `reward_amount` — INT\n- `is_active` — BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true\n- `created_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n\n**`bonus_completions`** (lines 127-134)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `user_id` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `bonus_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to completion_bonuses)\n- `period_key` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `completed_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n- **UNIQUE constraint:** `(user_id, bonus_id, period_key)`\n\n---\n\n### **2. DB Client Interface (src/db.ts)**\n\n**File path:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n#### **Transaction Support** (lines 674, 1861-1864)\n\n```typescript\n/** Execute a function within a database transaction.\n * All db methods called on the transactional Db share the same transaction.\n * Rolls back on error, commits on success.\n */\nasync withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>\n```\n\n**Implementation:**\n```typescript\nasync withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  return sql.begin(async (txSql: any) => fn(createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)));\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern:** Pass a function that receives a transactional `Db` instance. All queries in the function use the same transaction; rolls back on error, commits on success.\n\n#### **Raw SQL Access** (lines 676-678)\n\n```typescript\n/** Expose the underlying SQL/transaction handle for use with emitEvent(). */\n// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\nreadonly rawSql: any;\n```\n\n**What it is:** The underlying `postgres` client (from the `postgres` npm package). Used to:\n- Execute raw SQL queries with type safety via template literals\n- Access the transaction context when needed by event emission or other low-level operations\n\n**Usage pattern in db.ts:**\n- Queries use template literal syntax: `` await sql<Type[]>`SELECT ... WHERE x = ${value}` ``\n- Parameterized: values are passed via `${variable}`, not string concatenation\n- Returns arrays of typed rows\n- `sql.json()` for JSONB encoding\n- `sql.begin()` for transactions\n\n#### **Key Db Methods Relevant to Challenge Engine:**\n\nSince the schema is defined but no challenge-specific methods are exposed yet on the `Db` interface, you'll need to add them. The interface is at lines 319-682 of db.ts. The implementation pattern follows:\n\n1. **Query pattern:** `` await sql<Type[]>`SQL HERE` ``\n2. **Conflict handling:** `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` or `ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE`\n3. **Uniqueness protection:** UNIQUE constraints prevent duplicates at the DB level\n4. **JSON:** Use `sql.json()` for JSONB fields\n\n---\n\n### **GAME_SETTLED Handler Implementation Guidance**\n\nBased on the schema:\n\n**Key constraints to respect:**\n1. **progress_events UNIQUE(assignment_id, round_id)** — prevents double-counting progress from the same round\n2. **challenge_assignments UNIQUE(user_id, challenge_id, period_key)** — each player gets one active challenge assignment per period\n3. **bonus_completions UNIQUE(user_id, bonus_id, period_key)** — prevent duplicate bonus completions\n\n**Typical flow for GAME_SETTLED:**\n```\n1. Get game_entries for the round (from rounds/game_entries tables)\n2. For each entry (player):\n   a. Get active challenge_assignments for user_id + current period_key\n   b. For each assignment:\n      - Check if condition matches (scope, action, etc.)\n      - Try INSERT INTO progress_events(assignment_id, round_id, ...)\n        (UNIQUE constraint on (assignment_id, round_id) handles idempotency)\n      - If INSERT succeeds, UPDATE challenge_assignments.progress += progress_delta\n      - If progress >= target, UPDATE challenge_assignments.status = 'completed'\n   c. Check if all daily challenges completed → INSERT bonus_completion\n3. Grant points/crate rewards\n```\n\n**Use withTransaction() to ensure atomicity across all updates.**"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0816eb3-ec81-48b4-9f7e-e95cff86009e","uuid":"dc01c87d-66f3-4cb5-8435-2d50e2efa177","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:12:15.024Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the database schema for the challenge engine to implement the GAME_SETTLED handler. Please find and show me:\n\n1. `backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql` — the full migration with table schemas (especially challenge_assignments, progress_events, challenges, campaigns, completion_bonuses, bonus_completions)\n2. `backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` — the DB client interface, especially withTransaction and rawSql\n\nShow me the full contents of each file. I need to understand:\n- The exact column names and types for challenge_assignments, progress_events, challenges\n- How withTransaction works\n- How rawSql is used\n- The unique constraints on progress_events and challenge_assignments","agentId":"a7384c87dc889d660","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have the full picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary for you:\n\n## Database Schema & DB Client Reference\n\nHere's the complete information you need for implementing the GAME_SETTLED handler:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Challenge Engine Migration (011_challenge_engine.sql)**\n\n**File path:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql`\n\n#### **Key Tables:**\n\n**`challenge_assignments`** (lines 84-99)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `user_id` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `challenge_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to challenges)\n- `period_key` — TEXT NOT NULL (e.g., \"2026-04-03:daily\")\n- `status` — TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active' (CHECK: 'active', 'completed', 'expired')\n- `progress` — INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n- `target` — INT NOT NULL\n- `assigned_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n- `expires_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ\n- `completed_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ\n- **UNIQUE constraint:** `(user_id, challenge_id, period_key)`\n- **Indexes:** `idx_assignments_active` on `(user_id, status)` WHERE status='active'; `idx_assignments_period` on `(period_key, status)`\n\n**`progress_events`** (lines 102-111)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `assignment_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to challenge_assignments)\n- `round_id` — TEXT NOT NULL (from game settlement)\n- `user_id` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `progress_delta` — INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 1\n- `metadata` — JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'\n- `created_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n- **UNIQUE constraint:** `(assignment_id, round_id)` — **prevents duplicate progress from same game**\n\n**`challenges`** (lines 65-81)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `campaign_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to campaigns)\n- `title` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `description` — TEXT\n- `action` — TEXT NOT NULL (e.g., \"game_completed\", \"game_won\", \"lobby_filled\")\n- `scope` — TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'any' (CHECK: 'any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')\n- `condition` — TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'count'\n- `threshold` — INT NOT NULL\n- `reward_type` — TEXT NOT NULL (CHECK: 'points', 'crate')\n- `reward_amount` — INT\n- `prerequisite_id` — BIGINT (self-referential FK, nullable)\n- `eligible_if` — JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'\n- `sort_order` — INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n- `is_active` — BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true\n- `created_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n\n**`campaigns`** (lines 53-62)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `name` — TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE\n- `campaign_type` — TEXT NOT NULL (CHECK: 'daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding', 'dogpile')\n- `starts_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ\n- `ends_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ\n- `is_active` — BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true\n- `config` — JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'\n- `created_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n\n**`completion_bonuses`** (lines 114-124)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `campaign_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to campaigns)\n- `title` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `description` — TEXT\n- `required_count` — INT NOT NULL\n- `reward_type` — TEXT NOT NULL (CHECK: 'points', 'crate')\n- `reward_amount` — INT\n- `is_active` — BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true\n- `created_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n\n**`bonus_completions`** (lines 127-134)\n- `id` — BIGINT IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n- `user_id` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `bonus_id` — BIGINT NOT NULL (FK to completion_bonuses)\n- `period_key` — TEXT NOT NULL\n- `completed_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n- **UNIQUE constraint:** `(user_id, bonus_id, period_key)`\n\n---\n\n### **2. DB Client Interface (src/db.ts)**\n\n**File path:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n#### **Transaction Support** (lines 674, 1861-1864)\n\n```typescript\n/** Execute a function within a database transaction.\n * All db methods called on the transactional Db share the same transaction.\n * Rolls back on error, commits on success.\n */\nasync withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>\n```\n\n**Implementation:**\n```typescript\nasync withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  return sql.begin(async (txSql: any) => fn(createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)));\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern:** Pass a function that receives a transactional `Db` instance. All queries in the function use the same transaction; rolls back on error, commits on success.\n\n#### **Raw SQL Access** (lines 676-678)\n\n```typescript\n/** Expose the underlying SQL/transaction handle for use with emitEvent(). */\n// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\nreadonly rawSql: any;\n```\n\n**What it is:** The underlying `postgres` client (from the `postgres` npm package). Used to:\n- Execute raw SQL queries with type safety via template literals\n- Access the transaction context when needed by event emission or other low-level operations\n\n**Usage pattern in db.ts:**\n- Queries use template literal syntax: `` await sql<Type[]>`SELECT ... WHERE x = ${value}` ``\n- Parameterized: values are passed via `${variable}`, not string concatenation\n- Returns arrays of typed rows\n- `sql.json()` for JSONB encoding\n- `sql.begin()` for transactions\n\n#### **Key Db Methods Relevant to Challenge Engine:**\n\nSince the schema is defined but no challenge-specific methods are exposed yet on the `Db` interface, you'll need to add them. The interface is at lines 319-682 of db.ts. The implementation pattern follows:\n\n1. **Query pattern:** `` await sql<Type[]>`SQL HERE` ``\n2. **Conflict handling:** `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` or `ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE`\n3. **Uniqueness protection:** UNIQUE constraints prevent duplicates at the DB level\n4. **JSON:** Use `sql.json()` for JSONB fields\n\n---\n\n### **GAME_SETTLED Handler Implementation Guidance**\n\nBased on the schema:\n\n**Key constraints to respect:**\n1. **progress_events UNIQUE(assignment_id, round_id)** — prevents double-counting progress from the same round\n2. **challenge_assignments UNIQUE(user_id, challenge_id, period_key)** — each player gets one active challenge assignment per period\n3. **bonus_completions UNIQUE(user_id, bonus_id, period_key)** — prevent duplicate bonus completions\n\n**Typical flow for GAME_SETTLED:**\n```\n1. Get game_entries for the round (from rounds/game_entries tables)\n2. For each entry (player):\n   a. Get active challenge_assignments for user_id + current period_key\n   b. For each assignment:\n      - Check if condition matches (scope, action, etc.)\n      - Try INSERT INTO progress_events(assignment_id, round_id, ...)\n        (UNIQUE constraint on (assignment_id, round_id) handles idempotency)\n      - If INSERT succeeds, UPDATE challenge_assignments.progress += progress_delta\n      - If progress >= target, UPDATE challenge_assignments.status = 'completed'\n   c. Check if all daily challenges completed → INSERT bonus_completion\n3. Grant points/crate rewards\n```\n\n**Use withTransaction() to ensure atomicity across all updates.**"}],"totalDurationMs":46670,"totalTokens":53054,"totalToolUseCount":12,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1139,"cache_read_input_tokens":49835,"output_tokens":2075,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1139},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
