{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VJQ4sBf1vsrCZSieVM4qX6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document for you.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Backend Handler Patterns Reference\n\nI've gathered all the files you need to understand how to implement the GAME_SETTLED event handler. Here's your reference guide:\n\n### **File 1: Event Types** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`)\nDefines all event type constants. Your GAME_SETTLED handler listens to:\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n  // ... others\n} as const;\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 2: Challenge Adapters** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/challenge-adapters.ts`)\nThis is your adapter registry for evaluating challenge progress:\n\n**Key types:**\n- `GameSettledPayload` — the incoming event shape with `roundId`, `game`, `players[]`, `feeLamports`, `settledAt`\n- `GameSettledPlayer` — each player with `userId`, `wallet`, `amountLamports`, `isWinner` (null = refund), `isCreator`\n- `ChallengeAssignment` — challenge record with `action`, `scope` (game type filter), `condition`, `target`, `progress`\n- `VerificationAdapter` — pure function `(event, player, assignment) => AdapterResult`\n- `AdapterResult` — `{ shouldProgress: boolean, progressDelta: number }`\n\n**Quest eligibility gate:**\n```typescript\nexport function questEligible(player: GameSettledPlayer): boolean {\n  return player.isWinner !== null;  // Exclude refunds\n}\n```\n\n**Adapter registry** — three built-in adapters:\n1. `game_completed` — any settled game\n2. `game_won` — requires `isWinner === true`\n3. `lobby_filled` — requires `isCreator === true`\n\nGet an adapter by action: `getAdapter(action): VerificationAdapter`\n\n---\n\n### **File 3: Reward Pool Fund Handler** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.ts`)\n**Pattern example for simple state mutations:**\n\n**Factory pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport interface RewardPoolFundDeps {\n  db: Db;\n}\n\nexport function createRewardPoolFundHandler(deps: RewardPoolFundDeps) {\n  const { db } = deps;\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    // Validate payload fields\n    const roundId = payload.roundId as string;\n    const feeLamportsStr = payload.feeLamports as string;\n    if (!roundId || !feeLamportsStr) {\n      throw new Error(\"malformed payload — missing fields\");\n    }\n    \n    // Read config\n    const shareStr = await readRewardConfig(db, \"reward_pool_fee_share\");\n    const share = parseFloat(shareStr);\n    \n    // Calculate with proper precision\n    const fundedLamports = BigInt(Math.floor(Number(feeLamports) * share));\n    \n    // Transactional work\n    await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n      const inserted = await insertPoolFunding(txDb, roundId, feeLamports, fundedLamports);\n      if (!inserted) {\n        logger.info(\"duplicate round_id, skipping\", { roundId });\n        return;\n      }\n      await incrementRewardPool(txDb, fundedLamports);\n      logger.info(\"pool funded\", { roundId, fundedLamports: fundedLamports.toString() });\n    });\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key DB patterns:**\n- `db.rawSql` — execute raw SQL with template literals and automatic escaping\n- `db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {...})` — atomic transaction block\n- `ON CONFLICT (column) DO NOTHING RETURNING id` — idempotency check\n- Idempotency: insert + check for duplicate = safe re-processing\n\n---\n\n### **File 4: Points Grant Handler** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/points-grant.ts`)\n**Pattern example for computed grants with multipliers:**\n\n**Handler signature:**\n```typescript\nexport function createPointsGrantHandler(deps: PointsGrantDeps) {\n  const { db, getSolPrice } = deps;\n  \n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    let pointsAmount: bigint;\n    \n    if (sourceType === \"wager\") {\n      // Wager-based: lamports → USD → points\n      const amountLamports = Number(amountLamportsStr);\n      const wagerSol = amountLamports / 1e9;\n      const wagerUsd = wagerSol * solPrice;\n      const multiplier = await getActiveDogpileMultiplier(db, settledAt);\n      pointsAmount = BigInt(Math.floor(wagerUsd * pointsPerDollar * multiplier));\n    } else {\n      // Pre-calculated: use amount directly\n      pointsAmount = BigInt(amount);\n    }\n    \n    await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n      const inserted = await insertPointGrant(txDb, userId, wallet, sourceType, sourceId, pointsAmount, metadata);\n      if (!inserted) return;  // Idempotency\n      await upsertPlayerPoints(txDb, userId, wallet, pointsAmount);\n      logger.info(\"points awarded\", { userId, amount: pointsAmount.toString() });\n    });\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Upsert pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport async function upsertPlayerPoints(db: Db, userId: string, wallet: string, amount: bigint): Promise<void> {\n  await db.rawSql`\n    INSERT INTO player_points (user_id, wallet, balance, lifetime_earned, updated_at)\n    VALUES (${userId}, ${wallet}, ${amount}, ${amount}, now())\n    ON CONFLICT (user_id) DO UPDATE SET\n      balance         = player_points.balance + ${amount},\n      lifetime_earned = player_points.lifetime_earned + ${amount},\n      updated_at      = now()\n  `;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 5: Crate Drop Handler** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/crate-drop.ts`)\n**Pattern example for branching logic with nested transactions:**\n\n**Roll logic:**\n```typescript\nexport function createCrateDropHandler(deps: CrateDropDeps) {\n  const { db, rollRng = Math.random } = deps;\n  \n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    // Read all config upfront (outside transaction to minimize lock time)\n    const [solDropRateStr, pointsDropRateStr, solPoolPctStr, solMinValueStr, ...] = await Promise.all([\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"sol_crate_drop_rate\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"points_crate_drop_rate\"),\n      // ...\n    ]);\n    \n    const roll = rollRng();\n    \n    if (roll < solDropRate) {\n      // SOL crate path\n      await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n        // Lock the pool row for atomic updates\n        const pool = await lockAndReadRewardPool(txDb);\n        const poolBalance = BigInt(pool.balance_lamports);\n        \n        // Calculate payout\n        const payoutLamports = BigInt(Math.floor(Number(poolBalance) * solPoolPct));\n        \n        // Check suppression\n        if (payoutLamports < solMinValue) {\n          logger.info(\"SOL crate suppressed — pool below min\", { ...metadata });\n          return;  // Suppress without error\n        }\n        \n        // Insert (idempotency)\n        const inserted = await insertCrateDrop(txDb, userId, triggerType, triggerId, \"sol\", payoutLamports.toString());\n        if (!inserted) return;\n        \n        // Decrement pool\n        await decrementRewardPool(txDb, payoutLamports);\n        \n        // Emit downstream event\n        await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT, {\n          userId, wallet, payoutLamports: payoutLamports.toString(), triggerId,\n        });\n      });\n    } else if (roll < solDropRate + pointsDropRate) {\n      // Points crate path — emits POINTS_GRANT event\n      const pointsAmount = pointsCrateMin + Math.floor(rollRng() * (pointsCrateMax - pointsCrateMin + 1));\n      \n      await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n        const inserted = await insertCrateDrop(txDb, userId, triggerType, triggerId, \"points\", pointsAmount.toString());\n        if (!inserted) return;\n        \n        await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT, {\n          userId, wallet, sourceType: \"crate_points\", sourceId: `crate-${triggerId}`, amount: pointsAmount.toString(),\n        });\n      });\n    }\n    // else: miss (no drop)\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Locking pattern for concurrent safety:**\n```typescript\nexport async function lockAndReadRewardPool(db: Db): Promise<RewardPoolRow> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<RewardPoolRow[]>`\n    SELECT balance_lamports, lifetime_paid\n    FROM reward_pool\n    WHERE id = 1\n    FOR UPDATE  // ← Locks the row until transaction ends\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 6: Event Emission** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`)\n**How to emit downstream events from within a handler:**\n\n```typescript\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,  // Use txDb.rawSql from within a transaction\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }> {\n  const maxAttempts = options?.maxAttempts ?? 3;\n  const scheduledAt = options?.scheduledAt ?? new Date();\n\n  const rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n    VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload as postgres.JSONValue)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n  return { eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) };\n}\n```\n\n**Usage inside a transaction:**\n```typescript\nawait emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT, {\n  userId, wallet, sourceType: \"challenge_completed\", sourceId, amount: pointsAmount.toString(),\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 7: Handler Registration** (`backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`)\n**How handlers are wired up:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { createEventWorker, registerHandler, EventTypes } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { createRewardPoolFundHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.js\";\nimport { createPointsGrantHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/points-grant.js\";\nimport { createCrateDropHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/crate-drop.js\";\n\n// Register handlers BEFORE starting the event worker\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REWARD_POOL_FUND,\n  createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db }),\n);\n\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT,\n  createPointsGrantHandler({\n    db,\n    getSolPrice: async () => {\n      const result = await fetchSolPrice();\n      return result?.price ?? null;\n    },\n  }),\n);\n\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.CRATE_DROP,\n  createCrateDropHandler({ db }),\n);\n\n// Start the worker AFTER all handlers are registered\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 8: Event Queue Worker** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`)\n**How the event loop processes events:**\n\n1. **Polling** — every `pollIntervalMs` (default 1500ms)\n2. **Claiming** — `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` atomically claims batch of pending events\n3. **Dispatching** — calls registered handler with event payload\n4. **Idempotency** — handler should use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` to suppress duplicates\n5. **Retry logic** — exponential backoff (5s, 30s, 300s) on handler errors\n6. **Dead letters** — events exhausting retries marked as `dead` for manual review\n\n**Handler contract:**\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n```\n\nHandlers must be **idempotent** — safe to re-process if claimed multiple times.\n\n---\n\n## Key Patterns Summary\n\n| Pattern | Where Used |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **Factory function** | `createXxxHandler(deps)` returns async handler |\n| **Deps injection** | `db`, `getSolPrice`, `rollRng` passed to factory, not handler |\n| **Payload validation** | Throw error if required fields missing |\n| **Config reads** | Outside transaction to minimize lock time |\n| **Idempotency guard** | `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING RETURNING id` check |\n| **Transactions** | `db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {...})` for atomic ops |\n| **Lock & read** | `FOR UPDATE` inside transaction for concurrent safety |\n| **Event emission** | `emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventType, payload)` — pass txDb handle |\n| **Logging** | `logger.info()`, `logger.warn()`, `logger.debug()` for observability |\n| **BigInt math** | Use `BigInt()` for lamports, `Number()` for floats, then `BigInt()` result |\n\n---\n\n## Template for GAME_SETTLED Handler\n\nYour handler will:\n1. Accept `GameSettledPayload` as incoming event\n2. For each player in `players[]`:\n   - Check `questEligible(player)` — skip if refund\n   - Query challenge assignments for user\n   - For each assignment, get adapter via `getAdapter(assignment.action)`\n   - Call adapter to check if progress should increment\n   - If yes, emit `POINTS_GRANT` or other reward events\n3. Emit `REWARD_POOL_FUND` event for fee allocation\n4. Emit `CRATE_DROP` event for each player\n\nAll work inside `db.withTransaction()` for atomicity."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0816eb3-ec81-48b4-9f7e-e95cff86009e","uuid":"ce5bedb2-4a6e-4a95-a77e-6be0f66732fb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:12:33.147Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the existing code patterns in the backend to implement the GAME_SETTLED event handler (the orchestrator). This handler will process game.settled events, evaluate challenge progress, and emit reward events.\n\nPlease find and show me the contents of these files:\n1. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/challenge-adapters.ts` — the adapter registry and quest eligibility\n2. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.ts` — example of an existing handler pattern\n3. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/points-grant.ts` — another handler pattern\n4. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/crate-drop.ts` — another handler pattern\n5. `backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` — how handlers are registered\n6. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts` — event types\n\nFor each file, show me the full contents. I need to understand:\n- The handler factory pattern (createXxxHandler)\n- How DB transactions work (withTransaction, db.rawSql)\n- How emitEvent works\n- How the adapter registry is structured\n- The event types and payload shapes","agentId":"ad3ebfe96a598a7ca","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document for you.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Backend Handler Patterns Reference\n\nI've gathered all the files you need to understand how to implement the GAME_SETTLED event handler. Here's your reference guide:\n\n### **File 1: Event Types** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`)\nDefines all event type constants. Your GAME_SETTLED handler listens to:\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n  // ... others\n} as const;\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 2: Challenge Adapters** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/challenge-adapters.ts`)\nThis is your adapter registry for evaluating challenge progress:\n\n**Key types:**\n- `GameSettledPayload` — the incoming event shape with `roundId`, `game`, `players[]`, `feeLamports`, `settledAt`\n- `GameSettledPlayer` — each player with `userId`, `wallet`, `amountLamports`, `isWinner` (null = refund), `isCreator`\n- `ChallengeAssignment` — challenge record with `action`, `scope` (game type filter), `condition`, `target`, `progress`\n- `VerificationAdapter` — pure function `(event, player, assignment) => AdapterResult`\n- `AdapterResult` — `{ shouldProgress: boolean, progressDelta: number }`\n\n**Quest eligibility gate:**\n```typescript\nexport function questEligible(player: GameSettledPlayer): boolean {\n  return player.isWinner !== null;  // Exclude refunds\n}\n```\n\n**Adapter registry** — three built-in adapters:\n1. `game_completed` — any settled game\n2. `game_won` — requires `isWinner === true`\n3. `lobby_filled` — requires `isCreator === true`\n\nGet an adapter by action: `getAdapter(action): VerificationAdapter`\n\n---\n\n### **File 3: Reward Pool Fund Handler** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.ts`)\n**Pattern example for simple state mutations:**\n\n**Factory pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport interface RewardPoolFundDeps {\n  db: Db;\n}\n\nexport function createRewardPoolFundHandler(deps: RewardPoolFundDeps) {\n  const { db } = deps;\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    // Validate payload fields\n    const roundId = payload.roundId as string;\n    const feeLamportsStr = payload.feeLamports as string;\n    if (!roundId || !feeLamportsStr) {\n      throw new Error(\"malformed payload — missing fields\");\n    }\n    \n    // Read config\n    const shareStr = await readRewardConfig(db, \"reward_pool_fee_share\");\n    const share = parseFloat(shareStr);\n    \n    // Calculate with proper precision\n    const fundedLamports = BigInt(Math.floor(Number(feeLamports) * share));\n    \n    // Transactional work\n    await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n      const inserted = await insertPoolFunding(txDb, roundId, feeLamports, fundedLamports);\n      if (!inserted) {\n        logger.info(\"duplicate round_id, skipping\", { roundId });\n        return;\n      }\n      await incrementRewardPool(txDb, fundedLamports);\n      logger.info(\"pool funded\", { roundId, fundedLamports: fundedLamports.toString() });\n    });\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key DB patterns:**\n- `db.rawSql` — execute raw SQL with template literals and automatic escaping\n- `db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {...})` — atomic transaction block\n- `ON CONFLICT (column) DO NOTHING RETURNING id` — idempotency check\n- Idempotency: insert + check for duplicate = safe re-processing\n\n---\n\n### **File 4: Points Grant Handler** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/points-grant.ts`)\n**Pattern example for computed grants with multipliers:**\n\n**Handler signature:**\n```typescript\nexport function createPointsGrantHandler(deps: PointsGrantDeps) {\n  const { db, getSolPrice } = deps;\n  \n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    let pointsAmount: bigint;\n    \n    if (sourceType === \"wager\") {\n      // Wager-based: lamports → USD → points\n      const amountLamports = Number(amountLamportsStr);\n      const wagerSol = amountLamports / 1e9;\n      const wagerUsd = wagerSol * solPrice;\n      const multiplier = await getActiveDogpileMultiplier(db, settledAt);\n      pointsAmount = BigInt(Math.floor(wagerUsd * pointsPerDollar * multiplier));\n    } else {\n      // Pre-calculated: use amount directly\n      pointsAmount = BigInt(amount);\n    }\n    \n    await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n      const inserted = await insertPointGrant(txDb, userId, wallet, sourceType, sourceId, pointsAmount, metadata);\n      if (!inserted) return;  // Idempotency\n      await upsertPlayerPoints(txDb, userId, wallet, pointsAmount);\n      logger.info(\"points awarded\", { userId, amount: pointsAmount.toString() });\n    });\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Upsert pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport async function upsertPlayerPoints(db: Db, userId: string, wallet: string, amount: bigint): Promise<void> {\n  await db.rawSql`\n    INSERT INTO player_points (user_id, wallet, balance, lifetime_earned, updated_at)\n    VALUES (${userId}, ${wallet}, ${amount}, ${amount}, now())\n    ON CONFLICT (user_id) DO UPDATE SET\n      balance         = player_points.balance + ${amount},\n      lifetime_earned = player_points.lifetime_earned + ${amount},\n      updated_at      = now()\n  `;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 5: Crate Drop Handler** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/crate-drop.ts`)\n**Pattern example for branching logic with nested transactions:**\n\n**Roll logic:**\n```typescript\nexport function createCrateDropHandler(deps: CrateDropDeps) {\n  const { db, rollRng = Math.random } = deps;\n  \n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    // Read all config upfront (outside transaction to minimize lock time)\n    const [solDropRateStr, pointsDropRateStr, solPoolPctStr, solMinValueStr, ...] = await Promise.all([\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"sol_crate_drop_rate\"),\n      readRewardConfig(db, \"points_crate_drop_rate\"),\n      // ...\n    ]);\n    \n    const roll = rollRng();\n    \n    if (roll < solDropRate) {\n      // SOL crate path\n      await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n        // Lock the pool row for atomic updates\n        const pool = await lockAndReadRewardPool(txDb);\n        const poolBalance = BigInt(pool.balance_lamports);\n        \n        // Calculate payout\n        const payoutLamports = BigInt(Math.floor(Number(poolBalance) * solPoolPct));\n        \n        // Check suppression\n        if (payoutLamports < solMinValue) {\n          logger.info(\"SOL crate suppressed — pool below min\", { ...metadata });\n          return;  // Suppress without error\n        }\n        \n        // Insert (idempotency)\n        const inserted = await insertCrateDrop(txDb, userId, triggerType, triggerId, \"sol\", payoutLamports.toString());\n        if (!inserted) return;\n        \n        // Decrement pool\n        await decrementRewardPool(txDb, payoutLamports);\n        \n        // Emit downstream event\n        await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT, {\n          userId, wallet, payoutLamports: payoutLamports.toString(), triggerId,\n        });\n      });\n    } else if (roll < solDropRate + pointsDropRate) {\n      // Points crate path — emits POINTS_GRANT event\n      const pointsAmount = pointsCrateMin + Math.floor(rollRng() * (pointsCrateMax - pointsCrateMin + 1));\n      \n      await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n        const inserted = await insertCrateDrop(txDb, userId, triggerType, triggerId, \"points\", pointsAmount.toString());\n        if (!inserted) return;\n        \n        await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT, {\n          userId, wallet, sourceType: \"crate_points\", sourceId: `crate-${triggerId}`, amount: pointsAmount.toString(),\n        });\n      });\n    }\n    // else: miss (no drop)\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Locking pattern for concurrent safety:**\n```typescript\nexport async function lockAndReadRewardPool(db: Db): Promise<RewardPoolRow> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<RewardPoolRow[]>`\n    SELECT balance_lamports, lifetime_paid\n    FROM reward_pool\n    WHERE id = 1\n    FOR UPDATE  // ← Locks the row until transaction ends\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 6: Event Emission** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`)\n**How to emit downstream events from within a handler:**\n\n```typescript\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,  // Use txDb.rawSql from within a transaction\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }> {\n  const maxAttempts = options?.maxAttempts ?? 3;\n  const scheduledAt = options?.scheduledAt ?? new Date();\n\n  const rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n    VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload as postgres.JSONValue)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n  return { eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) };\n}\n```\n\n**Usage inside a transaction:**\n```typescript\nawait emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT, {\n  userId, wallet, sourceType: \"challenge_completed\", sourceId, amount: pointsAmount.toString(),\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 7: Handler Registration** (`backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`)\n**How handlers are wired up:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { createEventWorker, registerHandler, EventTypes } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { createRewardPoolFundHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.js\";\nimport { createPointsGrantHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/points-grant.js\";\nimport { createCrateDropHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/crate-drop.js\";\n\n// Register handlers BEFORE starting the event worker\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REWARD_POOL_FUND,\n  createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db }),\n);\n\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT,\n  createPointsGrantHandler({\n    db,\n    getSolPrice: async () => {\n      const result = await fetchSolPrice();\n      return result?.price ?? null;\n    },\n  }),\n);\n\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.CRATE_DROP,\n  createCrateDropHandler({ db }),\n);\n\n// Start the worker AFTER all handlers are registered\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File 8: Event Queue Worker** (`backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`)\n**How the event loop processes events:**\n\n1. **Polling** — every `pollIntervalMs` (default 1500ms)\n2. **Claiming** — `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` atomically claims batch of pending events\n3. **Dispatching** — calls registered handler with event payload\n4. **Idempotency** — handler should use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` to suppress duplicates\n5. **Retry logic** — exponential backoff (5s, 30s, 300s) on handler errors\n6. **Dead letters** — events exhausting retries marked as `dead` for manual review\n\n**Handler contract:**\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n```\n\nHandlers must be **idempotent** — safe to re-process if claimed multiple times.\n\n---\n\n## Key Patterns Summary\n\n| Pattern | Where Used |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **Factory function** | `createXxxHandler(deps)` returns async handler |\n| **Deps injection** | `db`, `getSolPrice`, `rollRng` passed to factory, not handler |\n| **Payload validation** | Throw error if required fields missing |\n| **Config reads** | Outside transaction to minimize lock time |\n| **Idempotency guard** | `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING RETURNING id` check |\n| **Transactions** | `db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {...})` for atomic ops |\n| **Lock & read** | `FOR UPDATE` inside transaction for concurrent safety |\n| **Event emission** | `emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventType, payload)` — pass txDb handle |\n| **Logging** | `logger.info()`, `logger.warn()`, `logger.debug()` for observability |\n| **BigInt math** | Use `BigInt()` for lamports, `Number()` for floats, then `BigInt()` result |\n\n---\n\n## Template for GAME_SETTLED Handler\n\nYour handler will:\n1. Accept `GameSettledPayload` as incoming event\n2. For each player in `players[]`:\n   - Check `questEligible(player)` — skip if refund\n   - Query challenge assignments for user\n   - For each assignment, get adapter via `getAdapter(assignment.action)`\n   - Call adapter to check if progress should increment\n   - If yes, emit `POINTS_GRANT` or other reward events\n3. Emit `REWARD_POOL_FUND` event for fee allocation\n4. Emit `CRATE_DROP` event for each player\n\nAll work inside `db.withTransaction()` for atomicity."}],"totalDurationMs":68511,"totalTokens":51890,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":267,"cache_read_input_tokens":47886,"output_tokens":3732,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":267},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
